     DDDDEEEESSSSCCCCRRRRIIIIPPPPTTTTIIIIOOOONNNN
          XXXXmmmmUUUUppppddddaaaatttteeeeDDDDiiiissssppppllllaaaayyyy provides the application with a mechanism
          for forcing all pending exposure events to be removed from
          the input queue and processed immediately.  When a user
          selects a button within a MenuPane, the MenuPanes are
          unposted and then any activation callbacks registered by the
          application are invoked.  If one of the callbacks performs a
          time-consuming action, the portion of the application window
          that was covered by the MenuPanes will not have been
          redrawn; normal exposure processing does not occur until all
          of the callbacks have been invoked.  If the application
          writer  suspects that a callback will take a long time, then
          the callback may choose to invoke XXXXmmmmUUUUppppddddaaaatttteeeeDDDDiiiissssppppllllaaaayyyy before
          starting its time-consuming operation.  This function is
          also useful any time a transient window, such as a dialog
          box, is unposted; callbacks are invoked before normal
          exposure processing can occur.

          _w_i_d_g_e_t      Specifies any widget or gadget.


























